## Test Patterns

### Mocking Dependencies
- Use framework-appropriate mocking (spies, stubs, fakes)
- Mock at the boundary (HTTP, database, external services)
- Provide realistic test data

### Async Testing
- Handle promises, observables, and callbacks correctly
- Use framework async utilities (fakeAsync, waitFor, etc.)
- Don't forget to await or tick

### Error Testing
- Test that errors are caught and handled properly
- Verify error messages and status codes
- Ensure no sensitive data leaks in error responses

## Checklist

- [ ] All public methods have test coverage
- [ ] Happy path scenarios covered
- [ ] Error/exception scenarios covered
- [ ] Authorization scenarios covered (if applicable)
{{#if patterns.isolation.enabled}}
- [ ] Data isolation scenarios covered
{{/if}}
- [ ] Edge cases tested (null, empty, boundary values)
- [ ] Async operations tested correctly
- [ ] Cleanup/destroy tested
- [ ] No hardcoded sensitive test data
- [ ] {{conventions.coverage_target}}%+ coverage achieved
